  "raw_response": "{\n  \"title\": \"Liquidity Sweep at Major Swing Low: Price Breaks Below Then Reverses Bullishly\",\n  \"school\": \"Smart Money Concepts (SMC)\",\n  \"asset\": \"EURUSD\",\n  \"timeframe\": \"1H\",\n  \"market_context\": \"Uptrend with imperfect structure; price approaches a major swing low that coincides with a key liquidity zone below prior long entries. The market is in a bullish bias but shows minor pullbacks.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"Price breaks below a major swing low located in a high-liquidity area, triggering stop losses, then reverses upward—this is a liquidity sweep, not a valid change of character.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Step 1: Identify the major swing low as the origin of a valid break of structure, confirmed by prior impulsive move and imbalance (FVG).\",\n    \"Step 2: Observe that this major swing low lies within a significant sellside liquidity pool (stop-loss cluster from prior longs).\",\n    \"Step 3: Note that price wicks below the major swing low but quickly returns inside the range, indicating a liquidity grab rather than true bearish momentum.\",\n    \"Step 4: Conclude the break is an invalid CHoCH due to liquidity sweep; the trend remains bullish and offers a long entry opportunity after the sweep completes.\"\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": null,\n  \"lessons\": \"A break below a major swing low is not a valid reversal if it occurs in a known liquidity zone; such sweeps are used by smart money to trigger retail stops before continuing the trend.\",\n  \"primary_image_frame_id\": \"5-pQbpg1Z0Q_f025",
